author: Staff Reports
title: KU’s Rychagova in tourney finals
text:
October 18, 2015 
Advertisement 
Stillwater, Okla.  Kansas University freshman Anastasiya Rychagova advanced to today’s title match with a pair of victories Sunday at the Intercollegiate Tennis Association Central Regionals. 
Rychagova downed Minnesota’s Carolina Ryba, 6-2, 6-1, in the quarterfinals and Oklahoma State’s 12th-ranked Viktoriya Lushkova, 6-4, 6-3, in the semis. 
“I do not even know where to begin with Anastasiya,” Kansas head coach Todd Chapman said. “I am so impressed with her. 
“It is amazing how poised and mature she is on the court in pressure situations, especially as a freshman.”
